  <p class="footer"><em>When researchers talk about neutron stars, dark matter, and gravitational lenses, they all start the same way: "Zwicky noticed this problem in the 1930s. Back then, nobody listened..."</em></p><p class="quote">Stephen Maurer about Zwicky.</p>
